Converting the datatype of columns: 'Created Date' and 'Closed Date' to DateTime¶

In [154]:
request_data['Created Date'] = pd.to_datetime(request_data['Created Date'], errors='coerce')

Statistical Testing¶

One way - ANOVA test to check whether the average response time across complaint types is similar or not¶

Importing f_oneway from scipy.stats¶
In [97]:
from scipy.stats import f_oneway

Null Hypothesis, H0: Average request closing times, i.e. response times, are similar across the complaint types¶

In [99]:
grouped_data = request_data.groupby('Complaint Type')['Request_Closing_Time'].apply(list)

f_stat, p_val = f_oneway(*grouped_data)

print(f"F-statistic: {f_stat}")
print(f"P-value: {p_val}")
if p_val < 0.05:
    print("Reject H0: At least one of the complaint types has a different average request closing time.")
else:
    print("Failed to reject H0: Average request closing times are similar across complaint types.")

from scipy.stats import chi2_contingency

contingency_table = pd.crosstab(request_data['Complaint Type'], request_data['Location Type'])


chi2, p, dof, expected = chi2_contingency(contingency_table)
print(f"p-value: {p}")
if p < 0.05:
    print("Reject H0: Complaint Type and Location Type are related.")
else:
    print("Failed to reject H0: Complaint Type and Location Type are not related.")
